symc.name: ILD_BLEND25
symc.desc: Draws the image, blending 25 percent with the system highlight color. This value has no effect if the image list does not contain a mask.

symc.name: ILD_BLEND50
symc.desc: Draws the image, blending 50 percent with the system highlight color. This value has no effect if the image list does not contain a mask.

symc.name: ILD_IMAGE
symc.desc: Set this flag if the overlay does not require a mask to be drawn. This flag causes ImageList_DrawEx to draw just the image, ignoring the mask.

symc.name: ILD_NORMAL
symc.desc: Draws the image using the background color for the image list. If the background color is the CLR_NONE value, the image is drawn transparently using the mask.

symc.name: ILD_TRANSPARENT
symc.desc: Draws the image transparently using the mask, regardless of the background color. This value has no effect if the image list does not contain a mask.
